and when it gets down
to the proof that you want it,

40:40.772 --> 40:43.006
that's where we cut it off at.

40:43.008 --> 40:44.007
All right, boss, it's done.
It's done.

40:44.009 --> 40:45.675
Cut it off
and put on some cap.

40:45.677 --> 40:47.410
[josh] let it rip, tater chip.

40:47.412 --> 40:51.181
With all eight of these pots,
we just made over 600 gallons

40:51.183 --> 40:53.716
of good liquor in one day.

40:53.718 --> 40:55.218
Damn, still is hot.

40:55.220 --> 40:57.854
Yeah, damn right,
that thing's scalding.

40:57.856 --> 41:01.558
But we're talking about
massive amounts
of liquor right here.

41:01.560 --> 41:03.460
All right, here we go, boys.

41:03.462 --> 41:05.628
This is gonna make our jobs
a whole lot easier.

41:05.630 --> 41:08.698
So what we're gonna do is,
henry's got this pump,

41:08.700 --> 41:11.768
we're just gonna pump it
over here into these totes

41:11.770 --> 41:13.269
and be out of here in no time.

41:14.306 --> 41:15.638
Here she comes.

41:15.774 --> 41:18.508
Things have changed
from back in the day
and doing this stuff.

41:18.510 --> 41:20.810
They'd be bucketing
all this up and trying
to get it out of here.

41:20.812 --> 41:22.479
And you know,
we got these pumps and stuff.

41:22.481 --> 41:25.114
I thought about how those
old-timers got all that stuff

41:25.116 --> 41:28.051
in and out of the woods
when they weren't using
vehicles.

41:28.053 --> 41:29.385
[kenny] some had mules.

41:29.387 --> 41:31.888
I knew someone,
he had a mule,
got caught five times.

41:31.890 --> 41:34.724
The law would turn up,
the mule got caught
more than anybody.

41:34.726 --> 41:37.093
[all laughing]

41:48.540 --> 41:51.040
oh, I hope that stuff's
ready to go, puss.

41:51.042 --> 41:52.642
We're coming in here
to run this rye this morning.

41:52.644 --> 41:53.843
Oh, yeah.

41:53.845 --> 41:56.713
-It ain't doing nothing.
